up to five girls in passing

37:09.268 --> 37:11.062
that Mal brought to his apartment.

37:11.437 --> 37:14.440
Dolores croaked three months ago.
Trent says, like, three months ago,

37:14.523 --> 37:18.236
Mal got different. Mal crossed a line.
Trent didn't want to know what.

37:18.444 --> 37:20.154
Started doin' girls in other places.

37:20.404 --> 37:22.698
Even with his trusty camera set up
at Trent's?

37:22.865 --> 37:24.617
When he took Dolores
to Atlantic City, Andy,

37:24.700 --> 37:27.453
he knew what he was gonna do.
He wanted Dolores dead.

37:28.412 --> 37:30.373
First time, he's a cautious perv.

37:30.957 --> 37:34.377
-He'll take it out of the jurisdiction.
-Oh, knows he's never doing it again.

37:34.543 --> 37:37.129
Comes after with his lawyer
with the story how it happened

37:37.213 --> 37:39.006
gettin' his hands clean
and his mind right.

37:39.090 --> 37:41.175
Next hard-on,
he needs to push it a little farther.

37:41.425 --> 37:42.927
Let me try it on my home field.

37:43.135 --> 37:45.930
Yeah, assuming he didn't croak
anybody in between.

37:49.725 --> 37:53.104
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)

37:56.983 --> 37:58.985
So, do you think
Cullinan tells Sinclair the truth?

37:59.110 --> 38:00.736
(SCOFFS) I think he lies...

38:01.529 --> 38:03.864
in response to Sinclair saying,
"Lie to me."

38:11.664 --> 38:14.041
Bobby'd get really crazy too. (INHALES)

38:14.583 --> 38:15.960
I wanted it to work with Leo.

38:16.919 --> 38:18.587
The boys really looked up to him.

38:19.630 --> 38:20.631
You're done?

38:20.715 --> 38:22.174
-They look up to Mark McGwire...
-(DIANE EXHALING)

38:22.258 --> 38:23.843
JILL: ...even more,
and I wouldn't take that crap

38:23.926 --> 38:24.927
off him, either.

38:27.513 --> 38:28.514
(SIGHS)

38:33.602 --> 38:35.187
So, you'll take him
to the tombs? (EXHALES)

38:35.396 --> 38:36.480
Yeah. We got him.

38:36.981 --> 38:39.108
(INHALES) Andy and Sorenson
will take him over, guys.

38:40.276 --> 38:41.986
Be a shame if Mr. Cullinan
couldn't get arraigned

38:42.069 --> 38:43.112
till tomorrow night.

38:43.279 --> 38:45.906
(INHALES) We'll see
what kind of backbone our DA has.

38:46.198 --> 38:49.618
-Anyways, good job.
-Yeah. Thanks, boss.

38:55.041 --> 38:56.042
Frosty lager?

38:57.168 --> 38:58.252
Nah.

38:59.295 --> 39:00.755
I'm gonna stick around a while, James.

39:02.590 --> 39:04.884
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

39:06.677 --> 39:08.387
Want to watch the mighty brought low?

39:08.888 --> 39:11.932
Nah. I... I... I'm gonna keep excavating
these notebooks. (CHUCKLES)

39:12.016 --> 39:15.311
You're gonna keep digging till you, uh,
find Roberts' original outfit?

39:15.811 --> 39:17.355
Ah, you might as well be thorough.

39:18.606 --> 39:21.567
The thought of Mr. Cullinan
penned with them lower social types...

39:21.859 --> 39:24.820
(SCOFFS) Get your jollies now
before that beady-eyed conehead

39:24.904 --> 39:26.572
starts doing his legal tricks.

39:29.241 --> 39:30.242
(SIGHS)

40:04.985 --> 40:08.155
MIKE: <i>Here I go,</i>
<i>trying to break my cherry.</i>

40:22.086 --> 40:24.547
Well, look who just walked in. (EXHALES)

40:29.176 --> 40:32.096
-Hiya, Mike.
-(LIPS SMACKING) What are you, Donna...

40:32.972 --> 40:36.809
moonlighting as a bill collector
besides being a PAA

40:36.892 --> 40:39.645
in the detective squad
of the police station house

40:39.728 --> 40:40.938
where I formerly worked?

40:41.522 --> 40:45.484
I don't got a second job,
nor even a first one just now.

40:48.237 --> 40:49.405
How'd that happen?

40:51.073 --> 40:52.074
I don't know.

40:52.658 --> 40:53.659
You tell me.

40:54.785 --> 40:56.287
What are you talking about, anyway?

41:07.715 --> 41:10.384
(CHUCKLES)
I guess I got somewhat of a crush on you,

41:11.260 --> 41:14.763
and I quit my job,
hoping you'd hire me. (CHUCKLES)

41:15.890 --> 41:18.017
Well, I'm flattered,
but it's a little slow

41:18.100 --> 41:19.810
with my shingle just up.

41:22.813 --> 41:24.773
You were always very truthful, Mike.

41:25.608 --> 41:27.359
You know, a lot of times, you...

41:28.235 --> 41:31.155
haven't got even a vague idea
what you're doin'.

41:31.530 --> 41:34.408
-Hmm.
-This is the first thing I've attempted.

41:35.910 --> 41:37.453
I was sittin' here...

41:38.496 --> 41:40.039
hoping a case begins.

41:52.259 --> 41:55.471
Maybe I'll be your lucky charm,
'cause I believe in you.

41:57.264 --> 41:58.516
You got shortcomings,

41:59.350 --> 42:02.603
but I've always known
you're trying to be a good person.

42:03.938 --> 42:06.774
(INHALES) I hope to be
an encouragement to you

42:07.024 --> 42:08.526
just sittin' at my desk.

42:10.402 --> 42:13.364
I guess everyone needs someone
to believe in them

42:13.447 --> 42:14.865
at the beginning of things.

42:19.995 --> 42:21.121
I'll believe in you...

42:22.289 --> 42:24.083
even when you don't believe in yourself.

42:25.543 --> 42:27.962
You definitely add to the furnishings.

42:36.053 --> 42:40.724
MIKE: <i>Use her to encourage the detective.</i>
<i>Uh. She can help him out, give him advice.</i>

42:41.058 --> 42:42.184
<i>You know, keep him going.</i>

42:43.310 --> 42:44.937
<i>She'll always cheer him up.</i>

42:46.564 --> 42:48.274
<i>Everyone likes a beautiful broad.</i>

42:50.651 --> 42:52.403
<i>Maybe I can do this.</i>

